      public void print(int i)
      Prints a formatted representation of the XML element and its attributes to the standard output stream. Recursively prints all child attributes with increased indentation
      Parameters:

    • write

      public String write(int i, StringBuilder sb)
      Writes a formatted representation of the XML element, including its attributes (if any), to the provided StringBuilder object.
      Parameters:
      i - The indentation level (number of spaces) used for formatting the output. A larger indent value creates a more indented output.
      sb - The StringBuilder object to which the formatted element representation will be appended.
      Returns:
      The complete String representation of the formatted XML element, retrieved from the StringBuilder object.

    • addTags

      public void addTags(int indent, StringBuilder sb)
      Appends the formatted opening and closing tags of the XML element to the provided StringBuilder object, along with the element's value (if any).
      Parameters:
      indent - The indentation level (number of spaces) used for formatting the output.
